als. Estimates of simulated\nefficiencies, number of reflections and acquisition time are presented and\ncompared to analytical calculations. Those are very promising results, giving a\ntotal efficiency for the detection of scintillation light in liquid argon of\n1.7$\\rm \\pm$0.3\\%. Comparison of the estimated total efficiency with a\npreliminary result from an experimental test with an ARAPUCA prototype made in\nBrazil is also presented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Apr 2018 00:51:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-17"}
