how that $\\overline{R}_{c}^{it}(D)$ for a two-sided\nsource ...,x(-1),x(0),x(1),... equals $R_{c}^{it}(D)$ for the associated\none-sided source x(1), x(2),.... This implies that, for the Gaussian quadratic\ncase, the practical zero-delay encoder-decoder pairs proposed by Derpich and\n{\\O}stergaard for approaching $R_{c}^{it}(D)$ achieve an operational data rate\nwhich exceeds $R_{c}^{it}(D)$ by less than $1+0.5 \\log_2(2 \\pi e /12) \\simeq\n1.254$ bits per sample.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Apr 2018 02:16:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-12"}
